{"case_id": "case-010-d4-28", "container": "HC2", "pipeline_depth": 4, "message": "12 weeks pregnant, chronic HTN on lisinopril. OB asks about medication change.", "latency_ms": 8690, "llm_calls": 2, "tokens_in": 282, "tokens_out": 272, "cost_usd": 0.0002055, "task_success": true, "abstained": false, "answer": "**Recommendation:** Lisinopril must be immediately discontinued in this 12-week pregnant patient. Lisinopril, an ACE inhibitor, is contraindicated in pregnancy due to significant fetal risks, including renal dysfunction, oligohydramnios, and fetal death, particularly with exposure from the second trimester onwards. Transition to a pregnancy-safe antihypertensive medication is urgently recommended. Preferred alternatives include labetalol, nifedipine, or methyldopa [American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG) and National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidelines, 2023].", "tool_calls": 0, "hop_metrics": [{"hop": "vector_ingress", "latency_ms": 2, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "cache_gate", "latency_ms": 0, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "analyze", "latency_ms": 4293, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 93, "tokens_out": 147, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "writer", "latency_ms": 4391, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 189, "tokens_out": 125, "tool_calls": 0}], "embed_count": 2, "cache_hit": true, "cache_score": 1.0000001192092896, "variant": "exact_repeat", "error": null}
